summary: This is an email chain from January 2019 between FBI agents discussing the need to schedule a teleconference regarding the Epstein case due to travel restrictions from a government shutdown. The New York FBI agents want to coordinate with Florida counterparts and their AUSAs.

events.title: Scheduled Epstein case teleconference
events.description: A teleconference is scheduled for 11 am to discuss the Epstein case between FBI agents from New York and Florida, and their respective AUSAs.

events.title: Government shutdown impacts travel
events.description: A government shutdown prevents FBI agents from New York from traveling to Florida for an in-person meeting regarding the Epstein case.

keyFacts: The document shows ongoing FBI investigation into Epstein in January 2019, prior to his arrest in July 2019.
FBI agents from New York's VCAC/Human Trafficking unit were involved in the case.
A government shutdown in early 2019 impacted the investigation by preventing travel for coordination.
The communication indicates coordination between New York and Florida law enforcement regarding the Epstein case.
